<darkcolour>A6416E</darkcolour><section><title>Modifiers: &lt;I&gt;very, really, quite, not very&lt;/I&gt;</title><sectiontitle>The words (&lt;I&gt;not&lt;/I&gt;) &lt;I&gt;very, quite&lt;/I&gt; and &lt;I&gt;really&lt;/I&gt; are modifiers. Use them in front of an adjective to make it stronger or weaker. Use &lt;I&gt;very&lt;/I&gt; and &lt;I&gt;really&lt;/I&gt; to make the adjective stronger.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_5_3_1.mp3</titlesound><text1>That car is expensive.</text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_5_3_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>That car is &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;very&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; expensive!</text1a><text2>His grandmother's old.</text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_5_3_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>His grandmother's &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;really&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; old.</text2a><titlesound2>ELEMGRAM_5_3_4.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>Use &lt;I&gt;quite&lt;/I&gt; or &lt;I&gt;not very&lt;/I&gt; to make the adjective weaker.</sectiontitle2><text3>My house is small.</text3><sound3>ELEMGRAM_5_3_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>My house is &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;quite&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; small.</text3a><text4>That motorbike is expensive.</text4><sound4>ELEMGRAM_5_3_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>That motorbike is&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;n't very&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; expensive.</text4a></section></grammar>